|YKOAlthough many languages exist on DarkWind, adventurers can get away, for
the most part, by using the language known as "common". The common tongue
originated among the humans living in and around the City of Darkwind,
and grew in popularity as the city gained in prominance in the affairs of
the world.

All players can automatically speak common, by using the |YKB"csay" |YKOcommand.
In addition, many socities are fluent in one or more other languages.
Some of these languages are racially based, while some are more regional
in nature. Players can speak in their native language using the |YKB"rsay"
|YKOcommand. Those that do not have a native language will speak in common.
It is possible for those of sufficient intellect to study at a language
academy and learn additional languages as well.

The |YKO"say" |YKOcommand will allow you to speak in your default language.
If you know more than just common, you can switch your default language
using the |YKB"set language" |YKOcommand.
